The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Midnapore, March 9: An 11-year-old girl and a woman were injured when supporters of the CPM and the Bhoomi Uchchhed Pratirodh Committee exchanged fire in Nandigram this evening. 

 Jharna Kajili, a Class VI student, and Nilima Das, 20, were hospitalised with bullet injuries. 

 Calcutta: Every Ben-gal MLA will soon get a laptop. The finance minister also announced a hike in the MLAs daily attendance allowance from Rs 350 to Rs 500.

 Calcutta: The chief minister denied know- ledge of any starvation death in the tea gardens of north Bengal. There may be problems because of malnutrition and lack of sufficient food, he said.

 Serampore: Shooter Seuli Sadhukhan, who was shot at on Wednesday, was stable on Friday. The hospital said her condition improved since the surgery to remove a part of the bullet. 




